<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-08-12 00:53 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Calif. To Call For Power Cutbacks  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES (AP) -- Temperatures over 100 degrees and increased
air conditioner use strained the region's power system Friday,
prompting a Stage Two power alert in which commercial users were
asked to cut back.
</P>
<P>
   A Stage Two Emergency is triggered when power reserves drop to
below 5 percent. The Independent System Operator, the agency in
charge of California's power grid, asked commercial users to
voluntarily cut back on power use from 4:30 p.m. to 8:30 p.m.
</P>
<P>
   A Stage Three Emergency -- when power reserves drop to below 1&AMP;frac12;
percent -- would include mandatory rolling power outages for all
customers.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER> AP-NY-08-12-00 0053 </TRAILER>
