<HEADLINE> Sunday's News Show Lineup  </HEADLINE>
By The Associated Press	   
<TEXT>
<P>
   Lineup for the Sunday TV news shows:
</P>
<P>
   ABC's ''This Week With Sam Donaldson and Cokie Roberts'' --
Topics: Campaign 2000, Clinton-Lewinsky. Guests: Sen. Joseph
Lieberman, D-Conn., Democratic vice presidential candidate; the
Rev. Jesse Jackson; Sen. John Breaux, D-La.; HUD Secretary Andrew
Cuomo; Maryland Lt. Gov. Kathleen Kennedy Townsend; Rep. Jesse
Jackson Jr., D-Ill.
</P>
<P>
   CBS' ''Face the Nation'' -- Topic: Campaign 2000. Guests: Sen.
Joseph Lieberman, D-Conn., Democratic vice presidential candidate;
Gore campaign chairman William Daley.
</P>
<P>
   NBC's ''Meet the Press'' -- Topic: Campaign 2000. Guests: Sen.
Joseph Lieberman, D-Conn., Democratic vice presidential candidate;
Patrick Buchanan, Reform Party presidential candidate.
</P>
<P>
   CNN's ''Late Edition With Wolf Blitzer'' -- Topic: Campaign 2000.
Guests: Sen. Joseph Lieberman, Democratic vice presidential
candidate; Karl Rove, Bush campaign chief strategist; Rep. David
Dreier, R-Calif., Bush California campaign chairman; Rep. Charles
Rangel, D-N.Y.; California Gov. Gray Davis; Maryland Lt. Gov.
Kathleen Kennedy Townsend; Sens. Christopher Dodd, D-Conn., and
Paul Wellstone, D-Minn.
</P>
<P>
   ''Fox News Sunday'' -- Topic: Campaign 2000. Guests: Sen. Joseph
Lieberman, D-Conn., Democratic vice presidential candidate: Sen.
Paul Wellstone, D-Minn.; William Daley, Gore campaign chairman.
</P>
</TEXT>
