<HEADLINE> New York man convicted in 1995 murder  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   FAYETTEVILLE, W.Va. (AP) - A New York man accused of killing a
bar owner has been convicted of second-degree murder.
</P>
<P>
   A Fayette County Circuit Court jury deliberated three hours
Friday before finding Miguel A. Quinones, 22, guilty in the 1995
shooting death of Christopher Dennis Reardon, 49, of Oak Hill.
</P>
<P>
   Reardon, who had owned bars in Beckley and Mount Hope, was found
shot to death June 19, 1995, in his van, which had pushed into a
creek. His head had been encased in a plastic bag.
</P>
<P>
   Quinones was the third of three New York men arrested for
Reardon's murder. Damien Bagut had earlier pleaded guilty to
second-degree murder and Miguel Angel Gonzales was convicted of
accessory after the fact. Quinones was 17 and both Bagut and
Gonzales were 16 at the time of the murder.
</P>
<P>
   Prosecutors said Reardon was shot in a house where the three
youths were dealing crack cocaine.
</P>
</TEXT>
