<HEADLINE> Leno Readies For Classic Car Show  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES (AP) -- Jay Leno is revving up for California's
premiere rich-man, richer-man classic car display.
</P>
<P>
   Leno, Nicolas Cage and Ralph Lauren are among the auto
enthusiasts heading up the California coast for the 50th
anniversary of the Pebble Beach Concours d'Elegance show on Aug.
20.
</P>
<P>
   ''This is the millionaires versus billionaires car show. It's
the more money than brains club,'' Leno said Friday. The ''Tonight
Show'' host has his own collection of more than 150 cars and
motorcycles.
</P>
<P>
   The international event attracts more than 15,000 enthusiasts
each year, including heads of car companies, designers and car
collectors.
</P>
<P>
   Cars range from $7 million Bugattis and Duesenbergs to
publishing magnate Robert E. Petersen's 1927 Rolls-Royce Phantom I
Town Car, formerly owned by Fred Astaire.
</P>
</TEXT>
