<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mother, Children Killed in Algeria  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   ALGIERS, Algeria (AP) -- A pregnant woman and three of her
children were shot and killed at a roadblock set up by an armed
group, Algerian media reported Saturday.
</P>
<P>
   The woman, her husband and their four children were returning
home to Algiers from a beach outing Friday when a group of armed
men opened fire on their car, the daily newspaper Liberte reported.
The attack occurred near El-Aouana, about 225 miles east of
Algiers, the capital.
</P>
<P>
   The father, a 46-year-old professor at the University of
Algiers, was shot in the stomach and head. He remained in critical
condition at a hospital in Jijel, the newspaper reported.
</P>
<P>
   One child, a seven-year-old girl, managed to escape the gunmen.
Her mother and three siblings, ages 18 months to 14 years, were
shot to death, the report said.
</P>
<P>
   This North African country is plagued by violence despite a
peace drive by President Abdelaziz Bouteflika. Some 100,000 people
have died since 1992, when military-backed authorities canceled an
election that a now-banned Islamic party was expected to win,
triggering an Islamic insurgency.
</P>
</TEXT>
