<HEADLINE> Arafat, Peres To Brief China  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   BEIJING (AP) -- Palestinian leader Yasser Arafat and Israeli
Cabinet minister Shimon Peres will visit Beijing this week to brief
Chinese leaders on the Middle East peace process, the official
Xinhua News Agency said Saturday.
</P>
<P>
   Arafat was to visit Monday at the invitation of President Jiang
Zemin, and Peres was to come Wednesday and stay for two days,
Xinhua said.
</P>
<P>
   Arafat, who was in Moscow on Friday, has been on a world tour
seeking backing for a sovereign Palestinian state since the
collapse of talks with Israeli Prime Minister Ehud Barak in the
United States last month.
</P>
