<HEADLINE> McDermott Talks of Tough Childhood  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES (AP) -- Dylan McDermott, star of the TV series ''The
Practice,'' has been leading a charmed life lately.
</P>
<P>
   But his childhood was anything but: his parents split before he
was 2, he lost his mother at age 5 and he grew up in a rough town
in Connecticut while his dad tended bar in New York City.
</P>
<P>
   ''I was not big. I've been punched out many many times,'' said
McDermott, 38, in the September issue of Movieline magazine. ''I'm
not happy that all this happened to me, but I learned from it.''
</P>
