   From his father, he learned how to tend bar, serving William
Hurt, John Belushi, Ray Sharkey and other famous people.
</P>
<P>
   ''When you're a kid and you see for the first time how famous
people are treated like royalty, how people give them things that
they don't give normal human beings, it's like, 'Whoa, this is
something I want. And need! How do you get that?'''
</P>
