<HEADLINE> Pilot killed in small plane crash  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   ROSEBOOM, N.Y. (AP) - A Schenectady man died when a small plane
he was piloting home after purchasing it in Illinois crashed in a
wooded area, deputies said.
</P>
<P>
   Ronald Wnuk, 58, bought the 1974 single-engine Grumman aircraft
on Thursday in Peru, Ill., and left Friday morning to fly it back
to Schenectady, the Otsego Sheriff's department said. It crashed at
8:20 p.m. Friday in this town just south of Cherry Valley.
</P>
<P>
   Investigator Richard Devlin said it is believed only Wnuk was
aboard.
</P>
<P>
   The weather and damaged trees forced investigators to call off
the search late Friday, but Wnuk's body was found in the wreckage
Saturday. An autopsy is planned.
</P>
<P>
   The Federal Aviation Administration and the National
Transportation Safety Board are investigating.
</P>
<P>
   Roseboom is 50 miles west of Albany.
