<SUBHEAD>
Bush, McCain Complete Western Tour
</SUBHEAD>
<P>
   PRESCOTT, Ariz. (AP) -- George W. Bush pledged today to ''restore the
military power of the United States'' as he and former rival John McCain
completed a three-day Western campaign tour. Both Bush and Sen. McCain, R-Ariz.,
sounded military themes, here in McCain's home state and earlier at a rally near
a naval complex in Everett, Wash. They were Bush's final campaign events before
he steps out of the spotlight for the Democratic National Convention.
</P>
<SUBHEAD>
Dalai Lama Holds Out Hope For Tibet
</SUBHEAD>
<P>
   QAZA, India (AP) -- From an ancient monastery in the Himalayas, the Dalai
Lama sent out a message of hope Saturday for Tibetans who live under what he
called aparthied-like conditions in China. The Bhuddist spiritual leader was
joined in prayers by thousands of Tibetans, Indians and foreigners who have
gathered for a 15-day ceremony in Key Gompa, a 1,000-year-old monastery near
India's border with Tibet. The Dalai Lama was leading the 15-day Kalachakra
initiation ceremony at the monastery. He spoke for an hour and 45 minutes to an
assembly of Indian, Tibetan and western journalists.
</P>
