working hard on issues. In an interview with The Associated Press, Clinton
defended her work on issues ranging from health insurance to education and
adoption. The first lady has been under attack in New York from her Republican
opponent, Rep. Rick Lazio, for lacking a public record. ''Just ask her one thing
that she's done for New York,'' has become a familiar Lazio refrain in the
highly competitive Senate race. Clinton said she has a record to run on.
</P>
