strengthened early today but forecasters predicted it would gradually weaken as
it moved over cooler waters. The hurricane was not expected to pose any threat
to land as it continued to move northeast over open ocean. Satellite estimates
indicated Alberto had maximum sustained winds peaking at 125 mph.
</P>
