<HEADLINE> Excerpts from interview with Hillary Rodham Clinton  </HEADLINE>
By The Associated Press	   Excerpts from an interview with first lady Hillary
Rodham
Clinton, who is running for the U.S. Senate from New York:
<TEXT>
<P>
   On her policy work behind the scenes at the White House and why
she is now beginning to stress it on the campaign trail:
</P>
<P>
   -''I want people to know that, because if someone's going to
claim I sat around eating bonbons for the last five or six years, I
think it's only fair that the truth come out.''
</P>
<P>
   On her speech Monday to the Democratic National Convention and
the Senate race in New York:
</P>
<P>
   -''One of the reasons that I'm so intent upon the Senate race in
New York is that I want to be partner with Al (Gore) and Joe
(Lieberman) in building on all the progress that we've made for
children in the last eight years.''
</P>
<P>
   On her opponent Rep. Rick Lazio's very brief appearance at the
Republican National Convention in Philadelphia:
</P>
<P>
   -''You know I'm proud to be a Democrat and I'm a Democrat
whether I'm in New York or Los Angeles. ... He seems to be
unwilling to be identified with the Republicans in New York and
certainly didn't want to be in Philadelphia. When he's in
Washington he's a very strong follower of the Republican
leadership. I find it curious that he doesn't seem to want New
Yorkers to know that.''
</P>
<P>
   On reports of tensions between the Clintons and the Gore
campaign:
</P>
<P>
   -''We are here to do everything we can to highlight the success
of the Clinton-Gore administration and promote the Gore-Lieberman
administration.''
</P>
<P>
   On Rep. Loretta Sanchez's decision to move a fund-raiser from
the Playboy Mansion:
</P>
<P>
   -''She did what the vice president asked her to do. It's his
convention and I think that's an appropriate response.''
</P>
<P>
   On whether she would return a campaign donation from Playboy's
Christie Hefner:
</P>
<P>
   -''Christie Hefner is someone who contributes to a lot of
different people and I don't find that inappropriate or
surprising.''
</P>
<P>
   On the Republican convention:
</P>
<P>
   -''We heard a lot about children in the other party's
convention, but their record doesn't match their rhetoric.''
</P>
<P>
   On her family:
</P>
<P>
   ''We are having a good time with our life. I'm having a great
time campaigning for the Senate.''
</P>
</TEXT>
