<HEADLINE> Profile of Nat Goldhaber  </HEADLINE>
By The Associated Press	   Nat Goldhaber, named as John Hagelin's Reform Party
running
mate, is a high-tech entrepreneur who describes his net worth as
''less than hundreds of millions of dollars.''
<TEXT>
<P>
   He owns about 6 percent of Mypoints.com, which acquired his
Cybergold, Inc. this month. Mypoints.com, an Internet marketing and
loyalty firm, is currently worth about $450 million, making
Goldhaber's share about $27 million.
</P>
<P>
   His worth is probably substantially higher than that. His salary
at Cybergold was nearly $121,000 a year, according to Securities
and Exchange documents. And he has headed several other start-up
companies. Leadership of such firms often comes with stock options.
</P>
<P>
   Goldhaber, a licensed pilot, owns two planes, a Cessna 414 and a
Citation jet, which he said he will use for campaigning.
</P>
<P>
   He grew up in Berkeley, Calif. and now lives in Oakland with his
wife, Marilyn, and their 12-year-old triplet sons.
</P>
<P>
   He received a bachelor's degree from the Maharishi International
University. Hagelin is chair of the physics department at the
Maharishi University of Management. Goldhaber also holds a master's
degree in education from the University of California, Berkeley.
</P>
</TEXT>
