<HEADLINE> 3 N.Y. Cops Shot in Standoff  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- A gunman shot and wounded three police officers
in a seven-hour standoff at his Brooklyn home before he was fatally
shot by police Saturday night, authorities said.
</P>
<P>
   One officer was listed in serious condition.
</P>
<P>
   The standoff started after the man's parents told police their
son had purchased several weapons on Friday and had told them he
intended to ''shoot and kill police officers,'' Mayor Rudolph
Giuliani said.
</P>
<P>
   When the first officers arrived, the man, identified by police
as Albert Alalouf, opened fire with a shotgun, hitting officer
Gregory John in the shoulder.
</P>
<P>
   Police shot Alalouf several hours later after he surprised two
officers and shot one in the face and the other in the leg. Neither
officer's injury was considered life-threatening, Detective Joseph
Pentangelo said.
</P>
<P>
   Three other officers were being treated for injuries that were
not gunshot-related, officials said.
</P>
<P>
   Authorities said the bulletproof vest that John, 32, was wearing
had saved his life. At least eight holes were visible where
fragments had torn into the Kevlar vest.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER> AP-NY-08-12-00 2218 </TRAILER>
