<HEADLINE> Fusion 4, Rapids 1  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   FORT LAUDERDALE, Fla. (AP) -- Welton and Roy Lassiter scored
goals a minute apart Saturday night as the Miami Fusion beat the
Colorado Rapids 4-1.
</P>
<P>
   Miami was leading 2-1 when Welton scored on a rebound in the
82nd minute after Rapids goalkeeper David Kramer saved a shot by
Lassiter.
</P>
<P>
   Lassiter scored his sixth goal of the year less than a minute
later to close out the scoring.
</P>
<P>
   Jim Rooney gave the Fusion (9-11-5) a 1-0 lead in the 37th
minute, sending a shot past Kramer from 15 yards out. Just three
minutes later, Andy Williams made it 2-0 when he put the ball in
the left side of the net, as Kramer was diving to the right.
</P>
<P>
   Marcelo Balboa cut the deficit to 2-1 in the 54th minute,
scoring past goalie Nick Rimando.
</P>
<P>
   The Fusion's four goals ties a franchise-record that was
accomplished four previous times. Miami swept the season series
with Colorado 3-0.
</P>
<P>
   Colorado (11-12-3) remained winless at Lockhart Stadium, the
only venue in the MLS in which the Rapids have not won.
