<DATE_TIME> 2000-08-12 22:22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Liberty 72, Mystics 63  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON (AP) -- Vickie Johnson and Tari Phillips scored 20
points apiece as New York held off Washington in Game 1 of the
Eastern Conference playoffs.
</P>
<P>
   The Liberty scored 10 of the game's last 12 points after the
Mystics closed to 62-61 on Nikki McCray's 3-pointer with 2:17 to
play. Phillips followed with a baseline move for a layup, and
Whitmore hit a pair of free throws.
</P>
<P>
   The top-seeded Liberty will be home for Game 2 on Monday night
in New York and for Game 3, if necessary, on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
   Johnson was 7-for-11 from the field and also had eight rebounds.
Vicky Bullet led Washington with 22 points and five blocks. Nikki
McCray had 15 points and 11 rebounds.
</P>
